spanGrp.span: ‘There were many dogs playing and one of them came out;
Mãĩ tã'ĩ chichi-wa tsõ jinõ je damĩũ e-gla jẽk yá-sã'
at that time a chicken also came out on the road.
jueta óshkoro yaba e-gla jẽk yá-sã' ñala kömĩ
At that moment an airplane [lit. something for us to fly] was passing by and carrying something that we plant;
jueta jirö (_) se jũnã-glö inga damãu-mĩ wã jirö töbie-gẽ se të je damitse-mĩ
it fell on top of the chicken, hitting it right on the head;
ñerö janã-mĩ óshkoro bata inga kenã' óshkoro tasgu mẽ
it hit [the chicken] and ended up by the dog.
So they began to play like we play ball;
(_) ñerö ñã kaga jinõ se jinõ bola wa
they began to play where all the others were.
jekepa í të ñã kaga jinõ jera mãĩ siga-wa tã'ĩ tsõ ska
At that moment there was a dog alone;
he then called the others to make a goal frame.
One of them played the goalkeeper and they began to play.
Jeme e-gla döá-wã í gugö Ñerö í ñã kaga jinõ
The ball hit the pig goalkeeper and got through the goal line.
je të mãĩ í pakká-wã-ite bi í demĩu tenã' kuchi mẽ kuchi mẽ í tenã'
Thus the pigs got happy because they wanted to eat it.
ñerö kuchi-wa kse-nã-tula-ka porke nã jie-wa biáte í kete-wã
They were setting it on fire uh but the dogs came and took it away from them.
Ñerö jie-wa tsõ-ka-nẽ í mõga nẽ yukö inga bi Ee chichi-wa demĩu-lo të í bagásã'-nẽ í yiga
Then they jumped onto the goal frame and dogs and pigs began to fight.
Ñerö jie-wa mẽ jie-wa ñã kichákka-tula-ka chichi jame kuchi ñã gagá-nẽ ñã bö
One climbed up, grabbed and hit a poor bird that was going by, bang!
Ñerö je kagõö bata inga të mãĩ dú pobre bö damãu kwãwã gugá-wã tiá ¡pö
So they crashed against one another.
Ñerö jie-wa bö kenã kíanã' ñã mẽ
And the bird fell down and collided against it.
Ñerö mãĩ dú (_) jã'nã-te kenã'-nẽ jie mẽ
There he grabbed and kicked it [the ball];
it went again toward the bird and hit it.
demĩu-nẽ puro e-gla dú mẽ… dú tiá-ite
The bird inflated because it swallowed the ball.’
Jeska (hm) dú wakke-nã'-ka porke dú jãrga í mẽnẽwãu
